description: sprint, also called dash, in athletics, a footrace over a short distance with an all-out or nearly all-out burst of speed
High jump, sport in athletics in which the athlete takes a running jump to attain height.
Hurdling, sport in athletics in which a runner races over a series of obstacles called hurdles, which are set a fixed distance apart.
The javelin throw is a track and field event where the javelin, a spear about 2.5 m (8 ft 2 in) in length, is thrown.
The long jump is a field event in athletics that combines speed, strength and agility. In the regular long jump.
